   "outputs": [],
   "source": "import re as _re, textwrap as _tw\n\n# ── Verbatim from agent/prompts.py (BASE_SYSTEM_PROMPT_WS) ──────────────────\n_BASE_SYSTEM_PROMPT_WS = _tw.dedent(\"\"\"\n      CRITICAL REASONING RULES - FOLLOW THESE BEFORE EVERY ACTION:\n\n      1. The incident alert in your first message contains the pipeline failure logs.\n         ALWAYS read to the end of the alert — the last line often contains a HINT:\n         that names the exact file to read and the fix to apply.\n         DO NOT call trigger_pipeline for discovery; it has already been run for you.\n\n      2. Read ONLY the file named in the failure output.\n         EXCEPTION: if the error is a docker build step failure (contains \"Step N/N : RUN\"\n         or \"returned a non-zero exit code\"), read Dockerfile — the requirements file is NOT\n         missing, it just has not been COPY'd yet due to wrong instruction order.\n         Do not read requirements.txt or app code for docker build failures.\n\n      3. write_file ALWAYS requires the COMPLETE new file content - not a diff.\n         Read the file first, then write the full corrected version.\n\n      4. MERGE CONFLICTS: if the error contains \"<<<<<<< HEAD\" or \"SyntaxError\" near\n         conflict markers, the file has unresolved git merge conflict markers.\n         Read the file with read_file, remove ALL three marker lines (<<<<<<< HEAD,\n         =======, >>>>>>> branch), keep the correct code, then write_file with the\n         clean resolved content.\n\n      5. If set_hypothesis returns 0.0 reward, your hypothesis is WRONG.\n         Re-read the incident alert logs and form a different hypothesis. Never repeat\n         one that scored 0.0.\n\n      6. Never repeat the exact same action+target twice in a row.\n\n      7. CASCADING FAULTS: after fixing and re-triggering, if the pipeline still fails,\n         treat the new error as a fresh independent root cause - re-read the new logs\n         and form a new hypothesis.\n\n      8. MANDATORY PROGRESSION: once you have called read_file and set_hypothesis,\n         your NEXT action MUST be write_file with the complete corrected file content.\n         Do NOT call read_file again on the same file. Do NOT call set_hypothesis again.\n         Do NOT call trigger_pipeline before write_file.\n\n    You are a CI/CD repair agent. The pipeline has already failed and you have been\n    paged with the failure logs. Debug and fix the fault using these tools ONLY:\n      - read_file      : read the specific file the failure log names\n      - set_hypothesis : declare your root-cause hypothesis before applying a fix\n      - write_file     : write the corrected file content to fix the fault\n      - trigger_pipeline : run the pipeline ONLY to verify a fix - not for discovery\n      - list_files     : list workspace files - only if the error references an unknown path\n      - finalize       : call when the pipeline passes to end the episode\n\n    Tool sequence (FOLLOW THIS EXACTLY - no deviations):\n    read_file -> set_hypothesis -> write_file -> trigger_pipeline -> finalize\n\n    NEVER call read_file twice on the same file.\n    NEVER call set_hypothesis more than once per fix attempt.\n    NEVER call trigger_pipeline before applying a fix via write_file.\n    NEVER call finalize unless trigger_pipeline returned status=passed.\n    NEVER write_file on a path you have not yet read_file.\n    NEVER use view_logs, inspect_config, rerun_pipeline, verify_fix - those tools do not exist here.\n    NEVER read files that the incident alert did not mention.\n\"\"\").strip()\n\n_GENERAL_SKILL_CARDS = {\n    \"Evidence-First Triage\": \"Read the file named in the incident alert before any hypothesis.\",\n    \"Hypothesis Quality\":    \"Hypotheses must mention concrete entities from the incident alert (file/line/error signature).\",\n    \"Safe Remediation\":      \"Apply minimal reversible fixes. Never disable checks or strip validations.\",\n    \"Verification Discipline\": \"After write_file, trigger_pipeline must follow before finalize.\",\n    \"Efficiency Control\":    \"Avoid repeated identical low-signal actions; switch tactic when a hypothesis is rejected.\",\n}\n\n_TASK_SKILL_CARDS = {\n    \"merge_conflict\": [\n        \"Error contains '<<<<<<< HEAD' or 'SyntaxError' at conflict marker line. File: services/api/routes.py.\",\n        \"read_file(services/api/routes.py) -> remove ALL three marker lines -> write_file with clean code.\",\n    ],\n    \"dependency_conflict\": [\n        \"Error names requirements.txt version conflict. File: services/api/requirements.txt.\",\n        \"read_file(services/api/requirements.txt) -> remove the exact pin causing the conflict -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"docker_order\": [\n        \"Error 'Step N/N : RUN pip install ... No such file' — Dockerfile build failure, NOT a missing file.\",\n        \"read_file(Dockerfile) -> move COPY line for requirements.txt BEFORE the RUN uv pip install line -> write_file(Dockerfile).\",\n    ],\n    \"flaky_test\": [\n        \"Error names tests/test_api.py::test_response_time_health with threshold too strict.\",\n        \"read_file(tests/test_api.py) -> find 'threshold = 0.001' -> change to 'threshold = 0.5' -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"missing_permission\": [\n        \"Error: network declared as external but could not be found. File: docker-compose.yml.\",\n        \"read_file(docker-compose.yml) -> remove 'external: true' from the network block -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"secret_exposure\": [\n        \"Error names services/api/app.py with hardcoded secret on a specific line.\",\n        \"read_file(services/api/app.py) -> replace literal secret value with os.environ.get('KEY') -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"env_drift\": [\n        \"Error: invalid port specification 'not-a-number:5000'. File: docker-compose.yml.\",\n        \"read_file(docker-compose.yml) -> fix the port value to a valid integer -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"invalid_database_url\": [\n        \"Error: psycopg2 connection failed, wrong port. File: .env (DATABASE_URL has wrong port).\",\n        \"read_file(.env) -> fix DATABASE_URL port from 15432 to 5432 -> write_file(.env).\",\n    ],\n    \"empty_secret_key\": [\n        \"HINT in alert: SECRET_KEY is empty in .env. File: .env.\",\n        \"read_file(.env) -> set SECRET_KEY to a non-empty value -> write_file(.env).\",\n    ],\n    \"missing_pythonpath\": [\n        \"Error: ModuleNotFoundError for services.runtime_support. File: .venv/runtime.pth.\",\n        \"read_file(.venv/runtime.pth) -> add '/app/services' on a new line -> write_file(.venv/runtime.pth).\",\n    ],\n    \"circular_import_runtime\": [\n        \"Error: ImportError circular import in services/api/runtime_probe.py.\",\n        \"read_file(services/api/runtime_probe.py) -> remove the FAULT_CIRCULAR_IMPORT_RUNTIME marker/import -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"missing_package_init\": [\n        \"Error: ModuleNotFoundError for services.runtime_support. File: services/runtime_support/__init__.py.\",\n        \"read_file(services/runtime_support/__init__.py) -> restore with minimal content -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"none_config_runtime\": [\n        \"Error: TypeError NoneType not subscriptable. FEATURE_CACHE_BACKEND is empty in .env.\",\n        \"read_file(.env) -> set FEATURE_CACHE_BACKEND=redis -> write_file(.env).\",\n    ],\n    \"log_pii_leak\": [\n        \"Error names services/api/routes.py with a log call emitting credential values.\",\n        \"read_file(services/api/routes.py) -> remove or mask the PII log statement -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"log_disabled\": [\n        \"Error: LOG_LEVEL hardcoded to CRITICAL in services/api/logging_config.py.\",\n        \"read_file(services/api/logging_config.py) -> change LOG_LEVEL from CRITICAL to INFO -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"bad_migration_sql\": [\n        \"Error: SQL SyntaxError 'CREAT TABLE' typo in db/migrations/001_init.sql.\",\n        \"read_file(db/migrations/001_init.sql) -> fix 'CREAT TABLE' -> 'CREATE TABLE' -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"schema_drift\": [\n        \"Error: undefined column 'artifact_url'. File: db/database.py has extra column in schema.\",\n        \"read_file(db/database.py) -> remove 'artifact_url' from CANONICAL_COLUMNS -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"terraform_invalid_provider\": [\n        \"Error: Failed to query provider 'invalidcorp'. File: infra/main.tf.\",\n        \"read_file(infra/main.tf) -> replace 'provider \\\"invalidcorp\\\"' block with valid provider -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"terraform_missing_variable\": [\n        \"Error: No value for required variable 'region'. File: infra/terraform.tfvars is empty.\",\n        \"read_file(infra/terraform.tfvars) -> add 'region = \\\"us-east-1\\\"' and other required vars -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n    \"terraform_permission_denied\": [\n        \"Error: AccessDenied for infra/main.tf. The file contains simulate_permission_denied flag.\",\n        \"read_file(infra/main.tf) -> remove the simulate_permission_denied line -> write_file.\",\n    ],\n}\n\n_OUTPUT_FORMAT = _tw.dedent(\"\"\"\n    OUTPUT FORMAT (STRICT - one ACTION line, nothing else after it):\n    Reason in <=2 short lines, then emit exactly one ACTION line as the LAST line:\n\n      ACTION: <op>|<target>|<value>\n\n    Where <op> in {read_file, write_file, list_files, trigger_pipeline, set_hypothesis, finalize}.\n\n    STATE MACHINE - you are always in one of these states, pick the matching action:\n      STATE A - no file read yet:         ACTION: read_file|<file from alert>|\n      STATE B - file read, no hypothesis: ACTION: set_hypothesis||<root cause>\n      STATE C - hypothesis set:           ACTION: write_file|<same file>|<COMPLETE corrected content>\n      STATE D - fix written:              ACTION: trigger_pipeline||\n      STATE E - pipeline passed:          ACTION: finalize||\n\n    Examples:\n      ACTION: read_file|.env|\n      ACTION: set_hypothesis||DATABASE_URL port is 15432, should be 5432 in .env\n      ACTION: write_file|.env|DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@db:5432/appdb\n      ACTION: trigger_pipeline||\n      ACTION: finalize||\n\n    CRITICAL: In STATE C, write_file value must be the COMPLETE file content.\n    Do NOT output read_file or set_hypothesis when in STATE C.\n\"\"\").strip()\n\n\ndef _get_system_prompt(fault_type: str = \"\") -> str:\n    base    = _BASE_SYSTEM_PROMPT_WS\n    general = \"\\n\".join(f\"- {k}: {v}\" for k, v in _GENERAL_SKILL_CARDS.items())\n    task_lines = _TASK_SKILL_CARDS.get((fault_type or \"\").lower(), [\"Use evidence-first debugging.\"])\n    task_section = \"\\n\".join(f\"- {l}\" for l in task_lines)\n    return (\n        f\"{base}\\n\\n\"\n        f\"Skill cards:\\n{general}\\n\\n\"\n        f\"Task-specific skills for '{fault_type}':\\n{task_section}\\n\\n\"\n        f\"{_OUTPUT_FORMAT}\"\n    )\n\n\n_VALID_OPS = {\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"trigger_pipeline\",\n              \"set_hypothesis\", \"finalize\"}\n_PLACEHOLDER_TARGETS = {\"?\", \"n/a\", \"\", \"none\", \"null\", \"-\"}\n\n\ndef _normalize_hypothesis(value: str) -> str:\n    return _re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", (value or \"\").strip().lower())\n\n\ndef _extract_hypothesis_from_prose(text: str) -> str:\n    for pat in [\n        r'(?:hypothesis|hypothesize)[:\\s]+[\"\\']?([^\\n\"\\']{20,200})',\n        r'(?:root.?cause|issue is|problem is)[:\\s]+([^\\n]{20,200})',\n    ]:\n        m = _re.search(pat, text, _re.IGNORECASE)\n        if m:\n            return m.group(1).strip().rstrip('.\")\\' ').strip()\n    return \"\"\n\n\ndef parse_action(text: str):\n    \"\"\"Parse the first ACTION line from the model response (first match wins).\"\"\"\n    matches = list(_re.finditer(r\"(?mi)^\\s*ACTION:\\s*([\\w_]+)\\s*\\|([^|\\n]*)\\|?(.*)$\", text))\n    if not matches:\n        return CICDAction(\"trigger_pipeline\", \"\", \"\")\n    m  = matches[0]\n    op, tgt, val = m.group(1).strip().lower(), m.group(2).strip(), m.group(3).strip()\n\n    if op not in _VALID_OPS:\n        return CICDAction(\"trigger_pipeline\", \"\", \"\")\n\n    if tgt.lower() in _PLACEHOLDER_TARGETS:\n        tgt = \"\"\n\n    if op == \"set_hypothesis\" and not val:\n        val = _extract_hypothesis_from_prose(text) or \"pipeline failure indicated by incident alert\"\n        tgt = \"\"\n\n    def _is_placeholder(v):\n        return bool(_re.fullmatch(r\"<[^>]{3,80}>\", (v or \"\").strip()))\n\n    if op == \"write_file\" and (not val or _is_placeholder(val)):\n        return CICDAction(\"read_file\", tgt, \"\")\n\n    if op in {\"trigger_pipeline\", \"finalize\"}:\n        tgt = \"\"\n        val = \"\"\n\n    return CICDAction(op, tgt, val)\n\n\nprint(\"System prompt + parser ready (repo-aligned with agent/prompts.py + agent/api_client.py)\")\nprint(\"Parse test:\", parse_action(\"ACTION: trigger_pipeline||\"))\nprint(\"Parse test:\", parse_action(\"Reasoning...\\nACTION: read_file|services/api/routes.py|\"))\n"
  },
